# 59_actions_zoom_nav_smoke — Tier 2 m9 View / Zoom / doc-nav sweep (s255).
# Validates the seven wrap-now zoom + document-navigation verbs migrated
# from raw `add_action` to `add_scripted_action`:
#   - Zoom: zoom-in / zoom-out / zoom-100 / zoom-200 / zoom-selection
#   - Nav:  doc-next / doc-prev
#
# Sibling smoke to 52-58, same conservative-shape posture. All seven are
# parameterless (no member storage, no sensitivity pump). Same shape as
# m3 / m4 / m6.
#
# **zoom-fit was already migrated in m2** (smoke 52 phase 6) — not
# repeated here. **toggle-rulers and toggle-outline are stateful bool
# actions** (`Gio::SimpleAction::create_bool`) and need wrapper-signature
# design work to support `win.toggle-rulers true`-style invocation;
# they're a fixture, NOT in this mechanical sweep.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Ten observables: 1 list + 7 invocations + 2 refusals.
#
# ── Caller / mask ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ScripterWindow listener, RunContext::Scripter. All seven verbs declare
# Scripter | TestRunner. Macro is OUT.
#
# ── Test isolation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Mutations:
#   - `win zoom-in`        — toolbar zoom-step +1.
#   - `win zoom-out`       — toolbar zoom-step -1. Cancels phase 2.
#   - `win zoom-100`       — zoom to 1× (artboard fits viewport).
#   - `win zoom-200`       — zoom to 2×.
#   - `win zoom-selection` — zoom to fit current selection (or no-op
#                            on empty selection).
#   - `win doc-next`       — cycles to next open doc (wraparound).
#   - `win doc-prev`       — cycles to prev (cancels phase 7).
#
# Net: after the run, zoom is at 2× then re-fit to selection, and the
# active doc is back to whatever it started as (next + prev cycle).
# Safe to run repeatedly. The first two pairs (in/out, next/prev) are
# internally idempotent; zoom-100 / zoom-200 / zoom-selection mutate
# zoom level but don't compound across runs.
#
# ── Precondition reminders ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Curvz running with project + doc open.
# 2. doc-next / doc-prev are most legible if 2+ docs are open in
#    the project. Trace channel passes either way.

